PREREQUISITES
	-> Python 2.5+ is installed on your system (http://www.python.org)
	-> Numpy 1.0.4+ is installed on your system (http://numpy.scipy.org/)
        -> SCons 0.98+ is installed on your system (http://www.scons.org)
                - Make sure your SCons libs are correctly installed into the PYTHONPATH.
                - For example add /sw/lib/scons-{version} to your PYTHONPATH.

QUICK INSTALLATION
	-> Installation into the default PYTHONPATH and PATH location:
		python setup.py install

CUSTOM INSTALLATION
	-> To install it into a specific location:
		python setup.py install --prefix=/path/to/location
		
		Where $SLIMPYINSTALL is /path/to/location of SLIMpy
		- Add $SLIMPYINSTALL/lib/python{version}/site-packages to $PYTHONPATH
		- Add $SLIMPYINSTALL/bin to $PATH

WORKING FROM SVN REPOSITORY
	-> Alternativly, if $SLIMpyCORE is the path to your working copy of SLIMpy core folder, you may
	just add these to your environment:
		Add $SLIMpyCORE to PYTHONPATH
			export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:$SLIMpyCORE
		Add $SLIMpyCORE/scripts to PATH
			export PATH=$PATH:$SLIMpyCORE/scripts


TESTING
	to test SLIMpy you can run python -c "import SLIMpy;SLIMpy.test()"


RUNNING THE PACKAGE
	-> Go into your python interpreter.
	-> Type "import SLIMpy" at your python command prompt.


